<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,1246,1302]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kluge" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[232,472,1246,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Fallceon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifolius">
<emphasis box="[232,472,1246,1270]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Fallceon longifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N." box="[821,993,1246,1270]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref25073" refString="Kluge, N. 1992 b. Efimeras cubanas de la familia Baetidae (Ephemeroptera) III: subgenero Fallceon del genero Baetis. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 71: 38 - 48. (In Russian)." type="journal article" year="1992">Kluge (1992b)</bibRefCitation>
from La Alcarraza and is easily distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waltz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1987" box="[590,694,1278,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Fallceon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,694,1278,1302]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Fallceon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its long, narrow gills.
</paragraph>
