<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[191,1441,1326,1510]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,309,1326,1350]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecology.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N." box="[476,650,1326,1350]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref25073" refString="Kluge, N. 1992 b. Efimeras cubanas de la familia Baetidae (Ephemeroptera) III: subgenero Fallceon del genero Baetis. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 71: 38 - 48. (In Russian)." type="journal article" year="1992">Kluge (1992b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Canizares, M." box="[662,869,1326,1350]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref24057" refString="Canizares, M. 1998. El orden Ephemeroptera en Cuba. Tesis de Grado, Universidad de Oriente; Santiago de Cuba. 42 p." type="book" year="1998">Cañizares (1998)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Benitez, Y." box="[931,1111,1326,1350]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref23888" refString="Benitez, Y. 2007. Revision del orden Ephemeroptera en los rios Yaquimo y Sevilla, Amancio, Las Tunas. Tesis de Grado, Universidad de Oriente; Santiago de Cuba. 56 p." type="book" year="2007">Benítez (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kluge" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[1123,1284,1326,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Fallceon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifolius">
<emphasis box="[1123,1284,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">F. longifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the low zones of rivers in backwaters that form along the banks, mainly in mud-bottom areas, and tolerates some degree of pollution. It has a limited altitudinal range, having never been collected above 
<quantity box="[1362,1439,1389,1413]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="250.0">250 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N." box="[201,358,1422,1446]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref25073" refString="Kluge, N. 1992 b. Efimeras cubanas de la familia Baetidae (Ephemeroptera) III: subgenero Fallceon del genero Baetis. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 71: 38 - 48. (In Russian)." type="journal article" year="1992">Kluge 1992b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Canizares, M." box="[369,562,1422,1446]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref24057" refString="Canizares, M. 1998. El orden Ephemeroptera en Cuba. Tesis de Grado, Universidad de Oriente; Santiago de Cuba. 42 p." type="book" year="1998">Cañizares 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N." box="[581,752,1422,1446]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref25073" refString="Kluge, N. 1992 b. Efimeras cubanas de la familia Baetidae (Ephemeroptera) III: subgenero Fallceon del genero Baetis. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 71: 38 - 48. (In Russian)." type="journal article" year="1992">Kluge (1992b)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the species for the months of February, March, May, June, July and October; to this we add January and suggest that adults may emerge at any time of the year.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[191,1442,1533,1686]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,533,1533,1557]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kluge" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[540,779,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Fallceon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longifolius">
<emphasis box="[540,779,1534,1558]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Fallceon longifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from the Eastern and Central-East Regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[324,389,1566,1590]" name="Cuba" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N." box="[404,560,1566,1590]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref25073" refString="Kluge, N. 1992 b. Efimeras cubanas de la familia Baetidae (Ephemeroptera) III: subgenero Fallceon del genero Baetis. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal 71: 38 - 48. (In Russian)." type="journal article" year="1992">Kluge 1992b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benitez, Y." box="[572,732,1566,1590]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref23888" refString="Benitez, Y. 2007. Revision del orden Ephemeroptera en los rios Yaquimo y Sevilla, Amancio, Las Tunas. Tesis de Grado, Universidad de Oriente; Santiago de Cuba. 56 p." type="book" year="2007">Benítez 2007</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[755,823,1565,1590]" captionStart="Figures 1–5" captionStartId="35.[192,287,1846,1868]" captionTargetBox="[215,1427,230,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-73@35.[196,1436,213,1826]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figures 1–5. Distribution records for Ephemeroptera in Cuba. 1) Major geographic regions of Cuba (Núñez 1989). 2) Americabaetis naranjoi, Callibaetis floridanus. 3) Cloeodes inferior, C. superior. 4) Caribaetis alcarrazae, C. planifrons, C. grandis. 5) Fallceon longifolius, F. poeyi, F. testudineus, F. sextus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5170693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5170693/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[893,996,1566,1590]" name="Jamaica" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naranjo, C. &amp; J. G. Peters" box="[1010,1319,1566,1590]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="83 - 91" refId="ref26473" refString="Naranjo, C., and J. G. Peters. 2016. New records of Ephemeroptera (Insecta) for Jamaica and the Dominican Republic. p. 83 - 91. In: M. Yoshimura and Y. Takemon (eds.). International Progress in Ephemeroptera and Plecoptera Research. Biology of Inland Waters, Supplement No. 3. 171 p." type="book chapter" year="2016">Naranjo and Peters 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Here we add two nymphs from Río Mayarí (Holguín Province) collected on 
<date box="[1015,1132,1598,1622]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" value="2001-01-28">28-I-2001</date>
by Aldana and Fonseca. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gonzalez-Lazo, D. &amp; F. F. Salles" box="[194,593,1630,1654]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="51 - 57" refId="ref24513" refString="Gonzalez-Lazo, D., and F. F. Salles. 2007. Description of a new species of Fallceon from Cuba, and redescription of the larva of F. longifolius (Ephemeroptera, Baetidae). Zootaxa 1583: 51 - 57." type="journal article" year="2007">González-Lazo and Salles (2007)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that a possible record from 
<collectingCountry box="[1060,1146,1630,1654]" name="Mexico" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(Lugo-Ortiz et al. 1994) was not this species.
</paragraph>
